"@Thanotos Omega":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/555d0e396368720c44095400#post_555d0e396368720c44095400
The thing that people tend forget is that Native Americans were developed societies at the time and had their own towns, societies and that.

It kind of legitimately pisses me off that so many places "teach" that native americans were "primitive" and they a lot of the time in public history books show native americans living in teepees and that to talk about them.

I think the reason why it pisses me off so much is that in high school during the part of history talking about native american culture I asked about their school system and oh god was the response cringeworthy.
